{#-
  Provenance footer (P6-C06 / ADR-308).

  Renders the full provenance block required by AN-30: input files with
  SHA-256 + mtime + shape, seed, timestamp, mode, library versions, active
  preferences. Optional blocks (sampling applied, anonymised columns,
  formula columns, analysis warnings) render only when present.

  ADR-307b bare-name policy: the template reads bare names
  (`mode`, `preferences`, `lib_versions`, `sample`, `anonymised_columns`,
  `formula_columns`) and the `provenance` object for the remaining fields
  that have no bare alias (`input_files`, `seed`, `timestamp`, `warnings`).

  Shared between hub.html.j2 and drillthrough.html.j2 so the footer stays
  conceptually unified (Brooks). Both hosts must keep the GVM attribution
  as the last child of <main> (shared rule 24, AN-31).
-#}
<section class="provenance" id="provenance">
  <h2>Provenance</h2>
  <dl>
    <dt>Input file(s)</dt>
    <dd>
      {% for f in provenance.input_files %}
        <code>{{ f.path }}</code> &middot; SHA-256: <code>{{ f.sha256 }}</code> &middot; {{ f.rows if f.rows is not none else '?' }} rows &times; {{ f.cols if f.cols is not none else '?' }} cols &middot; modified {{ f.mtime }}
      {% endfor %}
    </dd>
    <dt>Mode</dt><dd>{{ mode }}</dd>
    <dt>Random seed</dt><dd><code>{{ provenance.seed }}</code></dd>
    <dt>Run timestamp</dt><dd>{{ provenance.timestamp }}</dd>
    <dt>Library versions</dt>
    <dd>
      {% for name, version in lib_versions.items() %}
        {{ name }} {{ version }}{% if not loop.last %}; {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </dd>
    <dt>Active preferences</dt>
    <dd><code>{{ preferences | tojson }}</code></dd>
    {% if sample %}
      <dt>Sampling applied</dt>
      <dd>Sampled {{ sample.n_sampled }} of {{ sample.n_total }} rows (seed {{ sample.seed }})</dd>
    {% endif %}
    {% if anonymised_columns %}
      <dt>Anonymised input</dt>
      <dd>input appears anonymised &mdash; {{ anonymised_columns | length }} column(s) match token pattern: {{ anonymised_columns | join(", ") }}</dd>
    {% endif %}
    {% if formula_columns %}
      <dt>Excel-formula columns (cached values used)</dt>
      <dd>
        <ul class="provenance-formulas">
          {% for fc in formula_columns %}
            <li><code>{{ fc.column }}</code> &mdash; formula: <code>{{ fc.formula }}</code></li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </dd>
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
  {% if provenance.warnings %}
  <section class="provenance-warnings" aria-label="Analysis warnings">
    <h3>Analysis warnings</h3>
    <ul>
      {% for w in provenance.warnings %}
      <li>{{ w }}</li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
  {% endif %}
</section>
